theorem interior_closure_mono_of_subset_closure
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A B : Set X}
    (h : (A : Set X) ⊆ closure B) :
    interior (closure (A : Set X)) ⊆ interior (closure B) := by
  -- First, lift the inclusion `A ⊆ closure B` through the `closure` operator.
  have h₁ : closure (A : Set X) ⊆ closure B := closure_mono h
  -- Then apply the monotonicity of `interior`.
  exact interior_mono h₁

theorem interior_subset_closure_interior
    {X : Type*} [TopologicalSpace X] {A : Set X} :
    interior (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior A) := by
  simpa using
    (subset_closure :
      interior (A : Set X) ⊆ closure (interior A))
